Usage:
get_hmm_vision -f environment -r -s -h -p path -v size vq

-f specifies the object whose hmm will be created
-r creates the hmm using retrained data
-s shows the average probabilities after each iteration
-n number of states
-p path
-v size vq
-q name vector quantizer
-h shows this message

example:

./get_hmm_vision -f floor -n 9 -s -p /home/savage/observations/cmucam/training_hsi/ -v 64 -q all
